==English==

===Phrase===
'''[[fifteen]] [[minutes]] [[of]] [[fame]]'''

# Alternate form of [[15 minutes of fame]].
# {{idiom}} A very short time in the spotlight or brief flurry with fame, after which the person or subject involved is quickly forgotten.

===Etymology===
* '''1968:''' Andy Warhol, in a catalogue of an exhibition of his art in Stockholm
*:''In the future everyone will be world-famous for 15 minutes.''